city_market_intro.ai_prompt:
You are writing SEO content for {business}, a PMI Premier Authorized Training Partner offering live-virtual {service}.

Target page: {service} in {city}, {SS}
Target keyword: "{service} {city}"

City context (use this — do not invent facts):
- Key industries: {industries}
- Major employers actively hiring certified PMs: {top_employers}
- Salary context: {salary_note}
- Market background: {market_blurb}

Write a city market intro section with:
1. A heading (H2): 6–10 words, includes "{city}" and references the PM market or demand
2. Body: exactly 2 paragraphs, 160–190 words total
   - Para 1: Why this certification matters for {city} professionals specifically. Name 2–3 real local employers or industries.
   - Para 2: Career impact — salary and advancement in {city}. Reference the salary note. End forward-looking.

Rules: Use "{city}" 2–3 times across both paragraphs. Mention the certification name at least 3 times. Do not invent statistics, companies, or facts not provided. Flowing paragraphs only — no bullets.

Return JSON only, no explanation:
{"heading_text": "...", "text": "<p>...</p><p>...</p>"}

faq_additions.ai_prompt:
You are writing FAQ content for {business}, a PMI Premier Authorized Training Partner, for a {service} page targeting {city}, {SS}.

City context:
- Key industries: {industries}
- Major employers: {top_employers}
- Salary context: {salary_note}

Write exactly 2 city-specific FAQ items. These should answer questions a {city} professional would search for. Good topics:
- Certification salary in {city} or within a named local industry
- Certification job demand in {city} or at specific local employers
- How certification helps professionals in the dominant local sector
- How long training takes while working full-time in {city}

Each FAQ:
- question: a specific, searchable question (10–15 words), naturally includes "{city}"
- answer: 40–70 words. Reference real local context — industries, employers, or salary data above.

Return JSON only:
{"items": [{"question": "...", "answer": "..."}, {"question": "...", "answer": "..."}]}

city_spotlight.ai_prompt:
You are writing the "City Information" panel that appears beside a map of {city}, {state} on the website of {business}. This is a short, engaging, factual profile of {city} as a place — NOT a sales pitch for the business.

Write 1-2 short paragraphs, 90-140 words total, that give a visitor a vivid, accurate feel for {city}, {state}: its regional setting, what the local economy is built on, and a little local character. Tone: warm, confident, professional. Use fully original wording — do NOT copy encyclopedia phrasing or read like a Wikipedia entry.

GROUND EVERY SPECIFIC CLAIM ONLY IN THIS VERIFIED RESEARCH about {city} (do not introduce specifics beyond it):
- Regional / economic context: {market_blurb}
- Major employers: {top_employers}
- Key industries: {industries}
- Approximate population: {population}
- Verified local areas you MAY name (pick at most TWO, woven naturally into a sentence — never a "we serve X, Y, Z" list): {neighborhoods}

ACCURACY RULES (critical): Rely only on the verified facts above plus well-established general knowledge about {city}'s broader region and {state}. Do NOT invent or state as fact: statistics beyond the population above, distances or drive times, highway or route numbers, founding dates, named landmarks, climate figures, or any detail not supported by the research above. If a provided value is blank, simply omit that angle. If unsure about a specific detail for {city}, describe the broader region instead of inventing specifics. Use the standard two-letter abbreviation for {state} where it reads naturally. Mention {business} at most once and lightly, or not at all — keep the focus on the city.

Return JSON only, no markdown fences: {"mi_info_text": "the paragraph text; separate two paragraphs with a single blank line; plain text, NO HTML tags"}
